LAST WEEK KENNEDY MOVED FROM LA TO NY. JEDIDIAH BILA COVERED MONDAY AND TUESDAY BUT THERE WERE NO EPISODES WEDNESDAY AND THURSDAY. STOSSEL DIDN'T AIR EITHER, I'D GUESS 4th OF JULY IS WHY.

"Kennedy" is a news panel show hosted by Kennedy Montgomery. Kennedy Montgomery is a libertarian that you may recognize from 90's MTV, Stossel, and the Independents.

_,-'2_,-'2_,-'2_,-'2_,-'2_,-'2_,-'2_,-'2_,-'2_,-'2

Tonight's monologue - Jeb Bush says people need to work more. Media has a good ol' time.

Tonight's panel: JIM NORTON, MICHAEL MOYNIHAN, and AINSLEY EARHARDT. They continue to discuss Jeb Bush's recent comment. Donald Trump continues to be eloquent on the issue of race. He thinks he'll win the Latino vote.. some how.

The panel returns to talk about affirmative consent laws and consensual sex contracts.

DERRICK VAN ORDEN, author of "Book of Man" is in studio. High school drop out, decorated navy seal, talks what it is to be a man.

MTV releases decent looking documentary called "White people." It seems like it accomplishes it's stated goal of making people uncomfortable.

RICHARD HATCH (Survivor season 01 winner), ANDY GRIGNON (Original iPhone engineer) and  JANE ROOT ("The 2000's exec producer) are here to talk about the 2000's and an upcoming special on Nat Geo looking back on the 2000's.

MAILBAG
